parameters:
Clea: I came from the Adventurer's Guild. This is the
requested package.

Bar Owner: I thought Stolge would come, but are you girls
also members of the Adventurer's Guild?

Clea: I heard about the children of the pioneers from
Stolge.
Clea: How should I go about accepting the request?
Bar Owner: Sorry, but please accept it somewhere else.

Bar Owner: You saw the state of this run-down town, right?
We don't have the luxury to give jobs to outsiders.
Bar Owner: Besides, there's no job that women can handle.

Adventurer-like Woman: Hey, old man, are you saying that
women can't accept the request from the children of the
pioneers...?
Adventurer-like Woman: Are you saying that in front of me?

Bar Owner: Armada, who can give orders to the heroine of
Valeria other than you?

Adventurer Armada: I am Armada Valeria, an adventurer who
specializes in completing requests centered around Valeria.

Adventurer Armada: Hmph, a dream chaser who pursues ancient
civilizations.
Clea: Could you please allow us to take on the request?
Adventurer Armada: What is the purpose of the young lady?
Clea: We're here to subjugate the dragon.

Adventurer Armada: Hehe, so you're also a dream chaser. I
like that. Try completing a request from me.

Adventurer Armada: If you can successfully accomplish that,
you'll be free to take on requests in Valeria under my
responsibility.
Bar Owner: Sigh... Fine, do as you please.
Clea: Understood, what should we do?

Adventurer Armada: There were some idiots who held a grudge
against me, and when I thought they were completely
destroyed, they escaped to an abandoned mine.

Adventurer Armada: That's a good response. Hand them over to
the guards, but make sure not to kill them.

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Valeria Region/Crystal
Abandoned Mine\c[0]
Adventurer Armada: That expression, you did it, didn't you?
Clea: Yes, I have also informed the guards of Valier.

Adventurer Armada: There shouldn't be any complaints now,
right?

Bar Owner: Alright, I got it. You win. You're free to take
on any requests you want.

Bar Owner: Please check the bulletin board in the bar for
requests.
実績 流浪の冒険者

Adventurer Armada: By the way, I really like you! Actually,
I've been looking for a partner--
Stolge the Merciful: Please don't poach our potential members.
Adventurer Armada: Stolge! Long time no see, you look well.
Clea: Do you know each other?

Stolge the Merciful: Well then, when are you coming to the
Adventurer's Guild?
Adventurer Armada: Whenever your guild leader dies.
Adventurer Armada: Haha, just kidding. I'll be going soon.

Adventurer Armada: If you get tired of the Adventurer's
Guild, come to this bar and take on my requests.

Clea: They have a good vibe, but are they really
adventurers?

Stolge the Merciful: That's right, especially that person is
exceptional. Among the children of pioneers, there are three
major forces.

Stolge the Merciful: From the Wald region to the Gote Mycos
region, and then to the Valier region, Armada.

Clea: It seems that we need their permission in order to
accept requests, right?

Stolge the Merciful: You have good intuition. Well, there may be
times when we meet through guild requests.

Stolge the Merciful: That's right, this is the reward for
carrying luggage.

Stolge the Merciful: I'll go ahead, but since we're here, why
don't you try taking on some requests in Valier?

Stolge the Merciful: Once you're satisfied, please come to the
Adventurer's Guild. Agonia seems to have something to talk
about, so I'm counting on you.
Innkeeper: Lately, women have become strong and unbeatable.
Innkeeper: Are these Armada's favorite girls?
Clea: Where can I meet Armada-san?

Innkeeper: If it were up to me, I wish Armada-san didn't
have to live in such a remote village like Tulipa.
Innkeeper: Lately, women have become strong and unbeatable.

Innkeeper: Even in a run-down town like this, you can have
fun by drinking.

Explorer Armada: Let's wait with high expectations for the
results.

parameters:
Miner Rock: Hmm, are you adventurers? Could you do me a
favor and deliver this letter?
Clea: Understood, where should we go?

Miner Rock: Could you go to the Crystal Abandoned Mine and
deliver this? He has other deliveries to make, so he should
be able to make it in time!
Clea: Understood, I'll take care of it.

parameters: Innkeeper: If you're not ordering, please leave.

Up-and-coming gambler: 'I'm taking a moderate amount of
money from the customers here so they don't end up becoming
drunken fools.'

Rookie Gambler: Miss... would you like to play High and Low
with me?
Would you like to play High and Low by paying 600G?

Rookie Gambler: I guess it's fine for me to join the

Rookie Gambler: I'll take all the bets. Let's skip the

If you know someone with skill, please introduce them to me,

Rookie Mercenary: Miss... would you like to have a match

Rookie Mercenary: If you feel like it, give me a shout.

Rookie Mercenary: I can't believe I lost! I need to train

Rookie Mercenary: You had quite the skill for a woman.

parameters:
I never expected the young lady to bring the ancient map of
Valier.

Information Broker Leon: 'Did it bother you that the client
called you Miss Leon?'

Information Broker Leon: Can you show it to me right away?
Self-proclaimed adventurers often bring fakes, you know.

Information Broker Leon: The paper quality seems fine. Using
old paper for scams is a common trick even in spellbooks...
Information Broker Leon: Where did you guys get this?

Priestess Sophia: It's archaeologist Mr. Paryo. We obtained
it under special conditions.
Information Broker Leon: Mr. Paryo... Ahaha

Information Broker Leon: Ahahaha! Without a doubt, this is
the real deal. I finally got my hands on it!

Priestess Sophia: We are honored that you are pleased. We
will accept our reward and take our leave.

Information Broker Leon: Wait a moment! You must be
adventurers trusted by Paryo.

Information Broker Leon: Can you accept the additional
reward and take on the escort?

Clea: That's fine, but depending on the nature of the
request, we may have to decline.
Information Broker Leon: Exactly, my target is the prince!

Information Broker Leon: I'll be on the second floor of the
inn. I'll give you the reward for the map in advance.
Clea: How do you feel about the additional request?

Priestess Sophia: Oh my, I apologize! It's possible that
this could be some kind of trap.

Priestess Sophia: May I be entrusted with discerning the
nature of the request?
Clea: Understood. I will leave it to Sophia-san's judgment.

Information Broker Leon: Ah, I drank, I drank! My memory is
a bit fuzzy, but have we reached a conclusion?

Sophia the Priestess: I have made the decision to accept the

Clea: Understood. I will follow Sophia's judgment.

Information Broker Leon: That's right! I need you to come

Clea: So, you mean we'll be acting as escorts there?
Information Broker Leon: Ah, I don't know what will happen.
